Facebook Tech Talk - Scaling Analytics Solutions
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
*** UPDATE (3/1) *** We’re excited to announce that we’re providing a sneak peak of upcoming insights products and discussing the challenges of scaling analytics across the web. Tune in tomorrow to Facebook Live to join us. ------ Join Facebook Platform Engineer, Alex Himel, on Facebook Live to discuss the architecture and features behind Facebook’s analytics solutions. Hear how Facebook scaled our systems to handle billions of events across billions of sites per day, and the recent updates made to increase its effectiveness in optimizing site traffic for website owners. We’ll be streaming the Tech Talk live from the ‘Facebook Live’ tab at 7pm PDT! (http://www.facebook.com/FacebookLive) We invite you to ask questions via the ‘Ask A Question’ button (you can do so both in advance and during the Tech Talk).
Wednesday, March 2, 2011, 7 PM - 8 PM in PST
Online at Facebook Live - facebook.com/FacebookLive

Uprisings for Genuine Change
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Uprisings for Genuine Change (In solidarity with the people of Egypt and Burma) Join us for a roundtable conversation with some of the leaders of Burma’s 1988 student-led uprising and 2007 monk-led protests as we compare and discuss the current uprising in Egypt. Tentative agenda: 1) Discuss chronological history of current unfolding uprising in Egypt 2) Student leaders from 1988 uprising share their experiences 3) Monk leaders from 2007 Saffron protests share their experiences 4) Discuss social media roles and their significant contributions toward change 5) Compare and contrast between Egypt and Burma uprisings 6) How do we move forward in Burma? Following Burmese news was obtained from BurmaToday (www.BurmaToday.net) ********************** အီဂ်စ္နဲ႔ ျမန္မာႏိုင္ငံက အေရးေတာ္ပံုမ်ားအေၾကာင္း ႏွိဳင္းယွဥ္ ေဆြးေႏြးပြဲ - အီဂ်စ္ႏိုင္ငံမွာ လက္ရွိ ျဖစ္ေပၚေနတဲ့ ဆႏၵျပပြဲမ်ားနဲ႔ ျမန္မာႏိုင္ငံရဲ့ ၁၉၈၈ အေရးေတာ္ပံု၊ ၂၀၀၇ သံဃာ့လွဳပ္ရွားမွဳမ်ားအား ႏွိဳင္းယွဥ္ ေဆြးေႏြးပြဲတရပ္ကို 245 Sullivan Street, NY 11012 နယူးေယာက္တကၠသိုလ္ ဥပေဒေရးရာေက်ာင္းတြင္ ေဖေဖာ္၀ါရီ ၁၃ ရက္ (တနဂၤေႏြေန႔) ညေန ၅ နာရီမွ ည ၇ နာရီအထိ က်င္းပျပဳလုပ္ရန္ စီစဥ္ထားေၾကာင္း သိရပါတယ္။ ထို ေဆြးေႏြးပြဲမွာ ယခုျဖစ္ေပၚေနတဲ့ အီဂ်စ္ဆႏၵျပပြဲ ျဖစ္စဥ္၊ ျမန္မာႏိုင္ငံက ၁၉၈၈ အေရးေတာ္ပံု၊ ၂၀၀၇ သံဃာ့လွဳပ္ရွားမွဳအေၾကာင္း၊ မီဒီယာမ်ားရဲ့ အခန္းက႑၊ အီဂ်စ္နဲ႔ ျမန္မာ့အေရး ႏွိဳင္းယွဥ္သံုးသပ္ခ်က္၊ ေရွ႕အလားအလာမ်ားကို ေဆြးေႏြးသြားမွာ ျဖစ္ၿပီး တက္ေရာက္လိုသူမ်ားအေနနဲ႔ info@BurmaNetwork.com (သို႔) www.facebook.com/event.php?eid=189306771089362 သို႔ ဆက္သြယ္ႏိုင္ေၾကာင္း၊ တက္ေရာက္မယ့္သူမ်ားအေနနဲ႔ မိမိရဲ့ဓါတ္ပံုပါတဲ့ မွတ္ပံုတင္၊ အေထာက္အထားတခုခု ယူေဆာင္လာဖို႔ လိုအပ္ေၾကာင္း သိရပါတယ္။ ********************** *** Please make sure to bring a Photo ID for security check-in at the entrance. *** Closest subways: - A, B, C, D, E, F, M to West 4th Street - Washington Square station - N, R to 8th Street - NYU station *** Confirmed participants: - Venerable U Pyinya Zawta (2007 Saffron Revolution) - Moe Thee Zun, Nay Tin Myint (1988 Student-let uprising) Organized by Burma Global Action Network (www.Burma-Network.com) Media contact: TimAyeHardy@Burma-Network.com
